    <div class="container">
        <header id="header">
            <h1 style="text-align: center;"><i class="fas fa-om"></i> Birla Mandir</h1>
            <p>The magnificent white marble temple overlooking Hyderabad</p>
            <div class="hyderabad-badge">
                <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hyderabad, Telangana, India
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="main-image-container">
            <img src="https://media.tripinvites.com/places/hyderabad/birla-mandir/birla-mandir-hyderabad-featured.jpg"
                alt="Birla Mandir" class="main-image">
            <div class="image-overlay">
                <h2>"The Marble Jewel of Hyderabad"</h2>
                <p>Built in 1976 by the Birla Foundation</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> Historical Significance</h2>
            <p>Birla Mandir is a Hindu temple built entirely of white marble, dedicated to Lord Venkateswara (a form of Vishnu). Perched on a 280 feet high hill called Naubath Pahad, the temple offers panoramic views of Hyderabad city and the Hussain Sagar Lake.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                The temple was constructed by the Birla Foundation over a period of 10 years and was inaugurated in 1976 by Swami Ranganathananda of Ramakrishna Mission. The marble was sourced from Rajasthan.
            </div>

            <p>The temple complex features intricate carvings depicting scenes from Hindu mythology. The main shrine houses the idol of Lord Venkateswara, while smaller shrines are dedicated to deities like Shiva, Ganesh, Hanuman, and Brahma.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-archway"></i> Architectural Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Blend of Dravidian and Nagara architectural styles</li>
                <li>Constructed with 2000 tons of pure white marble</li>
                <li>40 feet high Gopuram (tower) at the entrance</li>
                <li>Detailed carvings of Hindu deities and mythological scenes</li>
                <li>Landscaped gardens surrounding the temple</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="nearby-section">
            <section class="restaurants" id="restaurants">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Nearby Vegetarian Restaurants</h2>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/5/18856175/9d1e5e0e1d8d7c0c0b5f4e4d5c5e5e5e.jpg"
                            alt="Chutneys" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Chutneys <span class="hyderabadi-badge">Pure Veg</span></h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Road No. 1, Banjara Hills (1.5 km from temple)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 7:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Masala Dosa, Idli Sambar, Filter Coffee
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/chains/1/18854041/9d1e5e0e1d8d7c0c0b5f4e4d5c5e5e5e.jpg"
                            alt="Minerva Coffee Shop" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-coffee"></i> Minerva Coffee Shop</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> SD Road, Secunderabad (3 km from temple)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 6:00 AM - 10:30 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Pesarattu Upma, Special Tea, Rava Dosa
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/4/18854044/9d1e5e0e1d8d7c0c0b5f4e4d5c5e5e5e.jpg"
                            alt="Udupi Upahar" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-leaf"></i> Udupi Upahar</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Himayatnagar (2 km from temple)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 6:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Set Dosa, Vada Sambar, Badam Milk
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/9/18854049/9d1e5e0e1d8d7c0c0b5f4e4d5c5e5e5e.jpg"
                            alt="Southern Spice" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-pepper-hot"></i> Southern Spice</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Jubilee Hills (4 km from temple)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Chettinad Veg Thali, Banana Leaf Meals
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://b.zmtcdn.com/data/pictures/7/18854047/9d1e5e0e1d8d7c0c0b5f4e4d5c5e5e5e.jpg"
                            alt="Taj Mahal Tea House" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-mug-hot"></i> Taj Mahal Tea House</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Abids (3 km from temple)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 6:00 AM - 10:30 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Bun Maska, Irani Chai, Osmania Biscuits
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="famous-places" id="attractions">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> Nearby Attractions</h2>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-JZw9xmZqObk/U_GZDZ70qsI/AAAAAAAAdKI/B7ObMOHE9A4/s1600/Hussain%2BSagar%2BLake%2Bhyderabad%2Bandhra%2Bpradesh%2Bindia.jpg"
                            alt="Hussain Sagar Lake" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-water"></i> Hussain Sagar Lake</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> 1.5 km from Birla Mandir</div>
                    <p>Iconic heart-shaped lake built in 1562 with a massive Buddha statue in the center. Popular for boating, evening walks, and the Lumbini Park laser show.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/images/visiting-places/headers/ntr-gardens-hyderabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg" 
                      alt="NTR Gardens" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-tree"></i> NTR Gardens</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> 800 m from Birla Mandir</div>
                    <p>Beautifully landscaped gardens with Japanese-style landscaping, a toy train, and a food court. Offers stunning views of Hussain Sagar Lake.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/images/places-to-visit/headers/nehru-zoological-park-hyderabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg"
                            alt="Nehru Zoological Park" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-paw"></i> Nehru Zoological Park</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 3 km from Birla Mandir</div>
                    <p>One of India's largest zoos, spread over 380 acres with over 1,500 species of animals, birds, and reptiles. Features safari parks and a butterfly park.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/images/places-to-visit/headers/state-archaeological-museum-hyderabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg"
                            alt="State Archaeological Museum" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-museum"></i> State Archaeological Museum</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 2 km from Birla Mandir</div>
                    <p>Established in 1930, this museum houses rare artifacts from various dynasties, including sculptures, paintings, and manuscripts.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/images/places-to-visit/headers/snow-world-hyderabad-tourism-entry-fee-timings-holidays-reviews-header.jpg"
                            alt="Snow World" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-snowflake"></i> Snow World</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-car"></i> 3 km from Birla Mandir</div>
                    <p>India's first snow-themed park, maintained at -5°C, featuring snow slides, a snow mountain, and a snow play area.</p>
                </div>
